      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SAPLING (2) her lone victory came at this trip and a win looks imminent third-up. Just over a month between runs when she closed well for a solid fourth over 1200m at Gosford in a fast-run contest. McEvoy sticks and expect to see her push forward today. Hard to hold out. RUSTEMO (1) finally shed his Maiden status first-up at start ten with a gritty on-pace win over 1300m at Scone. Re-unites with Jason Collett and he gets an even better set-up. Makes plenty of appeal. TURNING CIRCLE (8) is holding her form and showed plenty of grit with a fighting fifth over 1400m at Newcastle. Winning apprentice hops back aboard and can turn things around. KORITSI (6) bounced off her unlucky second with a tough win in the heavy (8) conditions over 1262m at Taree last time out. Drops in weight and has solid each-way claims.",
